<section xml:id="section-change-of-basis-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl>

	<li>
	<title>transition matrix</title>
	<idx>transition matrix</idx>
	<idx>change of basis matrix</idx>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>transition</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>change of basis</h></idx>
	<idx><h>basis</h><h>transition matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>basis</h><h>matrix, change of</h></idx>
	<p>
		the square matrix that converts between coordinate vectors relative to one basis <m>\basisfont{B}</m> of a finite-dimensional vector space and coordinate vectors relative to another basis <m>\basisfont{B}''</m> of that space;
		sometimes called the <term>change of basis matrix</term> for the two bases,
		and denoted <m>\ucobmtrx{B}{B'}</m>
	</p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
